The purposes of the Program are to:
Provide incentives for individuals to insure against the costs of providing for their long-term care needs;
Provide mechanisms for individuals to qualify for coverage of the costs of their long-term care needs under the medical assistance program without first being required to substantially exhaust all their resources;
Assist in developing methods for increasing access to and the affordability of a long-term care policy; and
Alleviate the financial burden on the State's medical assistance program by encouraging pursuit of private initiatives.
